00:22:15.720 --> 00:22:18.990
And my inspiration
to reach out to Arno

00:22:18.990 --> 00:22:23.310
was to figure out, OK, why
did this person do this?

00:22:23.310 --> 00:22:24.770
We weren't getting answers.

00:22:24.770 --> 00:22:27.360
So the best person
that can explain it

00:22:27.360 --> 00:22:30.060
is a person that has
lived that lifestyle

00:22:30.060 --> 00:22:34.170
and had started that same
organization to find out

00:22:34.170 --> 00:22:37.350
why somebody would do
something like this.

00:22:37.350 --> 00:22:39.300
And I didn't know
it at that time,

00:22:39.300 --> 00:22:42.000
but that would lead me to
my own personal feeling.

00:22:44.660 --> 00:22:47.240
Arno's not only my
friend and my brother.

00:22:47.240 --> 00:22:51.171
Arno is my counselor,
my therapist, and that's

00:22:51.171 --> 00:22:52.420
a lot coming from a therapist.

00:22:52.420 --> 00:22:56.145
ARNO MICHAELIS: I'm a therapist.

00:22:56.145 --> 00:22:58.510
PARDEEP KALEKA: And
I think we talk.

00:22:58.510 --> 00:23:02.620
We talk every week and
we talk about things that

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:04.720
are unrelated to August 5th.

00:23:04.720 --> 00:23:06.010
We're genuinely friends.

00:23:06.010 --> 00:23:07.540
We're genuinely brothers.

00:23:07.540 --> 00:23:11.560
This man comes over to my house,
babysits the kids, takes them,

00:23:11.560 --> 00:23:14.530
and all of that
to say, you really

00:23:14.530 --> 00:23:17.050
need to challenge-- we need
to challenge ourselves.

00:23:17.050 --> 00:23:19.570
And not to say that I'm not
putting any blame on the Wage

00:23:19.570 --> 00:23:21.350
Pages of the world.

00:23:21.350 --> 00:23:25.390
But if I put all the
blame and all the emphasis

00:23:25.390 --> 00:23:28.450
on the Wade Pages, the
white supremacists,

00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:31.000
the other people in
the world, then I

00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:33.550
continue to take my
life for granted.

00:23:33.550 --> 00:23:35.800
And I think the biggest part
of forgiveness is to say,

00:23:35.800 --> 00:23:36.780
you know what?

00:23:36.780 --> 00:23:39.780
Honestly, if this wouldn't have
happened, you would've went on

00:23:39.780 --> 00:23:41.770
and you would have
lived your life,

00:23:41.770 --> 00:23:44.410
and you wouldn't
have appreciated

00:23:44.410 --> 00:23:47.920
every single conversation
as much as you do now,

00:23:47.920 --> 00:23:50.710
every single relationship
that you do now.

00:23:50.710 --> 00:23:52.930
You probably wouldn't
tuck your kids in at night

00:23:52.930 --> 00:23:54.700
and hang around their
bed for an hour,

00:23:54.700 --> 00:23:57.150
and just sit there and watch
them sleep because you would

00:23:57.150 --> 00:23:58.390
have took that for granted.

00:23:58.390 --> 00:24:00.450
You probably wouldn't
have made love--

00:24:00.450 --> 00:24:07.020
oh, sorry-- made love with
a sense of appreciation.

00:24:07.020 --> 00:24:08.710
It's OK.

00:24:08.710 --> 00:24:11.430
We all know we do it.

00:24:11.430 --> 00:24:14.380
But in a way, I think the
forgiveness was really

00:24:14.380 --> 00:24:20.680
just like, OK, I need to take
control of my own personal life

00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:25.240
and our relationship
definitely helped that.

00:24:25.240 --> 00:24:27.220
