00:29:49.580 --> 00:29:50.970
What do I really want to know?

00:29:50.970 --> 00:29:52.590
What am I going to ask?

00:29:52.590 --> 00:29:54.620
I get all this other
stuff is going on,

00:29:54.620 --> 00:29:57.360
but now, we're face
to face, and what am I

00:29:57.360 --> 00:30:00.820
really going to ask him?

00:30:00.820 --> 00:30:04.990
And to my surprise, he was
kind of thinking the same way.

00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:08.830
He was like, what do I
say to this person who

00:30:08.830 --> 00:30:10.720
just lost their father?

00:30:10.720 --> 00:30:12.900
I'm sorry?

00:30:12.900 --> 00:30:16.650
I'm sorry would seem kind
of hollow at this point of I

00:30:16.650 --> 00:30:18.930
helped to start this
organization that this guy

00:30:18.930 --> 00:30:21.450
belonged to, and now
I'm sitting here,

00:30:21.450 --> 00:30:25.380
and I'm facing the consequences
of actions that I thought that

00:30:25.380 --> 00:30:30.330
I put way back there, but
knowing that I really can't.

00:30:30.330 --> 00:30:33.280
Like stuff that we
have done in the past,

00:30:33.280 --> 00:30:36.200
we still have to
be accountable for.

00:30:36.200 --> 00:30:39.350
Forgiveness doesn't mean
that we just move on

00:30:39.350 --> 00:30:42.350
and go forward with our life
without ever going back there

00:30:42.350 --> 00:30:44.000
and saying, you know what?

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:44.870
There's some wounds.

00:30:44.870 --> 00:30:45.930
There's some stuff back there.

00:30:45.930 --> 00:30:46.429
Right?

00:30:49.280 --> 00:30:52.970
Sometimes people say, well,
you know time heals all wounds.

00:30:52.970 --> 00:30:56.630
That's the biggest crock
of shit I've ever heard.

00:30:56.630 --> 00:30:59.330
Who made that saying?

00:30:59.330 --> 00:31:01.010
Time does not heal all wounds.

00:31:01.010 --> 00:31:04.460
In fact, sometimes, time
makes them worse, especially

00:31:04.460 --> 00:31:06.860
in an infected wound.

00:31:06.860 --> 00:31:08.660
Yes, we will go
on with our life,

00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:13.100
and if we got something
wrong, we can pad around that,

00:31:13.100 --> 00:31:15.520
and we can maneuver
our life around that.

00:31:15.520 --> 00:31:18.470
But if you're still moving
your life around that,

00:31:18.470 --> 00:31:20.120
this is still the focus.

00:31:20.120 --> 00:31:22.020
That wound is still the focus.

00:31:22.020 --> 00:31:25.670
Yeah, you've gone on, but
you haven't removed it.

00:31:25.670 --> 00:31:27.340
And that's the thing.

00:31:27.340 --> 00:31:30.220
Wounds do not heal with time.

00:31:30.220 --> 00:31:35.440
They heal with time,
they heal with purpose,

00:31:35.440 --> 00:31:37.810
they heal with
forgiveness, they heal

00:31:37.810 --> 00:31:39.790
with a sense of consciousness.

00:31:39.790 --> 00:31:47.780
They heal with honoring pain,
and the first time that we met,

00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:50.170
that's who I met.

00:31:50.170 --> 00:31:54.930
I met a person who said, listen,
we're going to honor this pain.

00:31:54.930 --> 00:32:00.520
We're going to be conscious
about what this pain is from.

00:32:00.520 --> 00:32:03.950
We're going to take
control of our lives.

00:32:03.950 --> 00:32:07.980
And that's how healing
wounds really happens.

00:32:07.980 --> 00:32:10.280
It's not just about time.

00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:11.480
It's about consciousness.

00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:12.680
It's about forgiveness.

00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:14.314
It's about purpose.

